<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUNTINGTON CONTINUES CHAMBER MUSIC SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Remaining events in the three-concert Huntington Library summer series by the 
Southwest Chamber Music Society take place Saturday and Aug. 13. 
</P>
<P>
 On Saturday at 7:30 p.m., in the Loggia of the Main Gallery, the ensemble 
continues its retrospective of the music of Charles Ives with a performance of 
his String Quartet No. 1, "The Revival Meeting." The agenda also lists Horatio 
Parker's String Quartet in F, piano music by Louis Moreau Gottschalk and rags 
by Scott Joplin. 
</P>
<P>
 On Aug. 13, the ensemble offers Ives' String Quartet No. 2, Mozart's "A 
Musical Joke" and Dvorak's "American" Quartet. 
</P>
<P>
 The Huntington Library is located at 1151 Oxford Road in San Marino. 
Information: (818) 405-2275). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA080594-0007 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 067012 </DOCID>
