<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRWIN R. BUCHALTER; LAW FIRM FOUNDER, EARL SCHEIB INC. CHAIRMAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irwin R. Buchalter, 84, founder of a major Los Angeles law firm and chairman 
of an automobile painting firm. A native of St. Paul, Minn., Buchalter earned 
his bachelor's degree at the University of Minnesota and his law degree at 
Southwestern University School of Law in Los Angeles.In 1947, he founded 
Buchalter, Nemer, Fields & Younger, a Los Angeles-based law firm that 
eventually added offices in San Francisco, San Jose, Newport Beach and New 
York. A longtime director and general counsel of Earl Scheib Inc., Buchalter 
became chairman of the well-advertised car painting firm when Scheib died in 
1992. Buchalter also served on the boards of Cedars-Sinai Medical Center, 
Southwestern University School of Law and the Jewish Federation Council and 
headed the United Jewish Fund's legal division. On Monday in Beverly Hills. 
