<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANCHEZ VICARIO, SWAMPED EARLY, RALLIES TO SURVIVE WERDEL SCARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After losing the first set in straight games, second-ranked Arantxa Sanchez 
Vicario rebounded to beat Marianne Werdel, 0-6, 6-4, 6-4, Thursday to reach the 
quarterfinals of the Toshiba Tennis Classic. 
</P>
<P>
 Werdel, ranked 49th, survived one match point on her serve to cut her deficit 
to 5-4 in the third set and then another in the next game before Sanchez 
Vicario closed the match on her serve. 
</P>
<P>
 Werdel, an eighth-year pro from nearby Oceanside, won 26 of 34 points in the 
first set, largely with sharp placement shots in her first meeting with Sanchez 
Vicario, the French Open champion. 
</P>
<P>
 The victory sets up Sanchez Vicario and Germany's Christina Singer in today's 
quarterfinals of the $400,000 event at La Costa Resort & Spa. Singer advanced 
with a 6-4, 6-0, victory over seventh-seeded Sabine Appelmans of Belgium. 
</P>
<P>
 Third-ranked Conchita Martinez topped Ginger Helgeson, 6-4, 6-3, and will face 
fifth-seeded Jana Novotna, who recorded a 6-0, 6-1 victory over ninth-seeded 
Iva Majoli in 41 minutes. Sixth-seeded Julie Halard also advanced, beating 
Natalia Medvedeva, 6-2, 6-3, for a quarterfinal matchup with top-ranked Steffi 
Graf. 
</P>
<P>
 In the late match, fourth-seeded Lindsay Davenport beat Ann Grossman, 6-1, 
6-2, but a muscle strain in her left leg could prevent her from meeting Tami 
Whitlinger-Jones, ranked 83rd. Whitlinger-Jones advanced when Angelica Gavaldon 
retired because of lower back strain with the score 6-2, 3-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
