<P>
NATIONAL LEAGUE ROUNDUP; ASTROS WIN THIRD IN A ROW OVER ROCKIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Scott Servais and Craig Biggio drove in two runs apiece in Houston as the 
Astros defeated the Colorado Rockies, 6-2, to earn their third consecutive 
victory over their most troublesome foe. 
</P>
<P>
 Darryl Kile (8-6) gave up eight hits and two runs in 6 2/3 innings as Houston 
won for only the seventh time in 24 games against Colorado. Kile struck out 
five and did not walk a batter. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Louis 7, Montreal 3 -- Bob Tewksbury gave up only five hits and Todd Zeile 
hit a grand slam as St. Louis ended the Expos' six-game winning streak with the 
victory in Montreal. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss, only the second for the NL East-leading Expos in their last 16 
games, ended the Cardinals' losing streak at four. 
</P>
<P>
 Tewksbury (12-10), 1-3 with a 9.43 earned-run average in his previous four 
starts, retired 10 in a row to start his fourth complete game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cardinals led, 3-1, entering the ninth, but Mel Rojas issued two walks 
around a single by Tewksbury, and Zeile cleared the bases with his 17th home 
run. It was his third career slam and sixth homer since the All-Star break. 
</P>
<P>
 Florida 5, Chicago 1 -- Mark Gardner gave up five hits in 7 2/3 innings and 
Gary Sheffield drove in three runs in Chicago as the Marlins won their third in 
a row over the Cubs. 
</P>
<P>
 Gardner held the Cubs hitless for 4 1/3 innings before Rick Wilkins singled.  
</P>
<P>
 Gardner (4-4) walked one and struck out four. Sheffield hit his 24th homer and 
had a two-run double. 
</P>
<P>
 Pittsburgh 5, Philadelphia 1 -- Jon Lieber held the Phillies to three hits in 
7 1/3 innings, and Dave Clark drove in two runs, as the Pirates won in 
Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
 Lieber (6-6) struck out six and walked one before he was relieved by Ravelo 
Manzanillo, who pitched 1 2/3 innings of hitless relief with three strikeouts. 
</P>
