<P>
YOUTH BASEBALL ROUNDUP; WESTOAKS POSTS 6-0 SHUTOUT AT AAU'S JUNIOR OLYMPICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Westoaks Senators defeated the Washington Arsenal, 6-0, Thursday behind 
the complete-game pitching of Bill Treese in the AAU Junior Olympics 
16-year-old division at Cocoa Beach, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
 Westoaks, composed of players from Thousand Oaks and Westlake Highs, is 3-3 in 
the 40-team tournament and concludes play today with a doubleheader. 
</P>
<P>
 Westoaks could finish fifth in the tournament with a sweep. 
</P>
<P>
 Westoaks has defeated the Virginia Mudcats (1-1) and the Cincinnati Pirates 
(12-2), and lost to the Cincinnati Hurricanes (6-4), the Knoxville Smokeys 
(2-1) and Southeast Wisconsin (5-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Right-hander Tim Baron is 2-0 and left-hander Micah Weathers has not allowed 
an earned run for Westoaks. Both pitchers are from Thousand Oaks High. Treese 
is from Westlake High. 
</P>
<P>
 Hitting leaders are Ryan Holmes (.588 batting average), Ryan Lane (.474), 
Baron (.385) and Steve Udell (six runs batted in). 
</P>
<P>
 The Senators participated in opening ceremonies at Space Center Stadium on 
Wednesday along with 10,000 other participants of the Junior Olympics. 
</P>
<P>
 Westoaks qualified for the Junior Olympics by winning a regional tournament in 
February. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge 23, Vista National 6 -- The Northridge Little League 12-year-old 
all-star team will advance to the Southern California Division final Saturday 
at 7 p.m. after crushing Vista behind home runs by Nathaniel Dunlap, Matt 
Fisher, Jonathan Higashi and Peter Tuber. Fisher was five for five with six 
RBIs. Tuber's home run was a grand slam and he has hit homers in three straight 
games. 
</P>
