<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: TURNER SHOOTS AN 81, FALLS 10 SHOTS BEHIND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Turner of Sherman Oaks shot an 81 Thursday in the third round of the 
Pacific Coast Amateur Championship at Bear Creek Golf Club in Murrieta, Calif., 
and fell 10 shots off the lead with one round to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Turner, one of the last players to tee off, was caught in the late-afternoon 
heat and wind and was eight over for the first eight holes. He has a 54-hole 
total of 223 after starting the round only two shots off the lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Claborn of Brea and Mark Johnson of Helendale are the co-leaders at 213. 
Turner, a four-time Southern California Public Links champion, is in a two-way 
tie for 27th place. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Darren Angel of Northridge shot his second consecutive one-over 71 and is tied 
for 14th place after three rounds of the American Junior Golf Assn. Boys' 
Junior Championship at the Four Seasons Resort Tournament Players Course in 
Irving, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
 Angel has a 54-hole total of even-par 210 and trails leader Robert Floyd of 
Miami Beach by nine shots. Ben Cherney of Encino shot 80 and dropped into a 
two-way tie for 58th at 227. 
</P>
