<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
WORKSHOPS ON REDUCING QUAKE DAMAGE OFFERED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free workshops offering tips on reducing property damage from an earthquake 
are being offered by the Federal Emergency Management Agency and state Office 
of Emergency Services. 
</P>
<P>
 Workshops on non-structural mitigation measures, such as securing water 
heaters, will be held at 6:30 p.m. Tuesday at the Crenshaw earthquake service 
center, 3420 W. Jefferson Blvd.; 6:30 p.m. Aug. 16 at 20525 Nordhoff St., 
Chatsworth; 10 a.m. Aug. 20 at 6939 Van Nuys Blvd., Van Nuys; 6:30 p.m. Aug. 23 
at 13750 Foothill Blvd., Sylmar, and 10 a.m. Aug. 27 at 552 Sespe Ave., 
Fillmore. 
</P>
<P>
 Workshops on strengthening rental units will be held at 6:30 p.m. Tuesday at 
28460 Stanford Ave., Valencia; 10 a.m. Thursday at the Sylmar location; 10 a.m. 
Aug. 20 in Fillmore; 6:30 p.m. on Aug. 23 at 6385 Hollywood Blvd., and 10 a.m. 
on Aug. 27 at 59 Tierra Rejada in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Workshops for strengthening homes will be held at 10 a.m. Thursday at the 
Crenshaw location; 6:30 p.m. Aug. 16 in Van Nuys; 10 a.m. Aug. 20 in 
Chatsworth; 6:30 p.m. Aug. 23 in Fillmore and 10 a.m. Aug. 27 in Sylmar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
