<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
FULL MTA FLEET EXPECTED TO BE ON STREETS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Metropolitan Transportation Authority bus service was nearly back to normal 
Thursday with the entire 1,900-bus fleet expected to hit the street today. 
</P>
<P>
 MTA officials predict a 5% drop in riders because of the nine-day strike by 
union mechanics, which was settled Wednesday. No post-strike ridership figures 
were immediately available, however. 
</P>
<P>
 The fare -- normally $1.10 -- will remain at 50 cents through Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
