By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A rapidly spreading wildland fire in the Sierra just west of Verdi exploded to 
about 1,200 acres Thursday in its first five hours and damaged or destroyed 
three homes, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The homes were among a handful of custom houses at the Sierra foothills. At 
least three were damaged or lost along with three outbuildings, fire 
spokeswoman Carol Burcell said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Crystal Peak fire was reported shortly before 2 p.m. and raced through 
about 1,000 acres on the California side of the state line before it was three 
hours old, said Tahoe National Forest spokesman Jerry Kent in Truckee, Calif. 
