<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; COUNCIL VOTES TO CREATE FIRE BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council this week voted to join other cities in creating a proposed 
governing body for the Orange County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 City Manager George Scarborough told the council that San Juan Capistrano was 
one of the last cities to consider taking part in the proposed joint powers 
authority before the issue goes to the Board of Supervisors. 
</P>
<P>
 If formed, the governing body would be launched this fall and assume full 
responsibility for the Orange County Fire Department, which serves several 
cities, including San Juan Capistrano. Each participating city would have a 
voting member on the authority's board of directors. 
</P>
<P>
 According to a city staff report, 85% of the Orange County Fire Department's 
service area is within cities. The department also provides services for 
unincorporated parts of the county. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
