<P>
MAN SERIOUSLY HURT IN FALL FROM SECOND-STORY WINDOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 21-year-old Huntington Beach man was seriously injured early Thursday when 
he toppled backward out a second-story window, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Christopher Todd had been out drinking with friends in Newport Beach on 
Wednesday night, Sgt. Andy Gonis said.After stops at Snug Harbor and 
Margaritaville, Todd purchased beer from a convenience store and returned to a 
friend's second-floor apartment in the 200 block of 33rd Street. 
</P>
<P>
 About 1:45 a.m., Todd "was walking inside the residence and leaned back and 
fell out the window" to the sidewalk below, Gonis said. The window was open, 
and he went through a screen. Tests indicated that Todd was legally drunk, 
Gonis said. 
</P>
<P>
 The young man was taken to Western Medical Center-Santa Ana, where he was 
reported in serious condition, police said. 
</P>
