<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SEMINAR TO ADDRESS NEW PESTICIDE RULES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Growers are invited to attend a free seminar that will bring them up-to- date 
on new federal regulations dealing with pesticide use and worker safety. 
</P>
<P>
 The seminar is scheduled for 8:30 a.m. Aug. 18 in the lower plaza assembly 
auditorium at the Ventura County Government Center in Ventura. 
</P>
<P>
 The talk will help farmers, nursery growers and greenhouse owners sort through 
regulations that became law in January, said horticulturist Julie Newman, an 
adviser in the Ventura office of the UC Cooperative Extension, a forum sponsor. 
</P>
<P>
 People who harvest, for example, must undergo safety training, as well as 
those who spray pesticides, she said. And workers will have to wait longer to 
enter a field after it has been sprayed with pesticide, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration for the seminar begins at 8 a.m. on Aug. 18. The forum is 
expected to run for about two hours, Newman said. For more information, call 
Newman at 645-1459. KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</TEXT>
