<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: RED CROSS CHAPTER AIDS RWANDA RELIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARYL KELLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a slow start, the Ventura County chapter of the American Red Cross has 
raised more than $4,000 since July 20 in relief funds for Rwandan refugees. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian E. Bolton, chapter executive director, said that donations have stepped 
up since world attention began to focus last month in the flight of more than 1 
million Rwandans into Zaire. 
</P>
<P>
 "We only received one donation of $40 until July 20," Bolton said. The chapter 
made its first Rwandan aid request May 1. 
</P>
<P>
 Bolton said people did not originally contribute because they thought 
"whatever they could do would not be enough to have an impact." 
</P>
<P>
 But that is not true, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 "Somebody making a donation of $7 is going to provide enough food to feed one 
person for a month," he said. "For $70 we can treat 35 cholera patients to save 
their lives." 
</P>
<P>
 Contributions should be sent to: "Rwanda Relief" c/o American Red Cross, P.O. 
Box 5850, Ventura 93005-5850. Or call 1-800-842-2200 to charge to Visa, 
MasterCard or American Express. DARYL KELLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
