<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; FATHER HELD AFTER BARRICADING CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 33-year-old Oxnard man has been arrested after holding police at bay for 
five hours, threatening to kill his four children and shattering the windows of 
his house, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Eugene Everett Luna was taken into custody about 11:30 p.m. Wednesday after a 
police SWAT team forced its way into the house and found Luna asleep in his 
living room. 
</P>
<P>
 Luna was booked into Ventura County Jail on suspicion of vandalism and willful 
cruelty to a child. He was being held in lieu of $5,000 bail, according to the 
jail watch commander. 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard police said the incident began with a fight between Luna and his mother 
at the family's home in the 500 block of East Yucca Street. When officers 
arrived about 6:35 p.m., Luna had barricaded himself inside and was threatening 
to kill his children, ages 2 to 10, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 As police tried to negotiate with Luna, three of his children escaped. Angry 
that police would not send the children back into the house, Luna began 
destroying the interior of the house and smashing out glass windows, according 
to Sgt. Dan Christian. 
</P>
<P>
 The SWAT team rescued the fourth child while entering the home to arrest Luna. 
JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
