<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SUN VALLEY; TRUCK JACKKNIFES ACROSS FREEWAY LANES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ABIGAIL GOLDMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A tractor-trailer heading north on the Golden State Freeway jackknifed 
Thursday morning when an out-of-control car ran into it, forcing the big rig 
over the concrete center divider with its trailer sprawled across the remaining 
lanes of traffic, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 There were no injuries in the accident, which began when Chun Yung of Los 
Angeles had problems with a tire shortly after 9 a.m. while driving in the fast 
lane.Yung lost control of his car and careened into the path of the truck, said 
Officer Mark Garrett of the California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 The truck's driver, Jesus Zepeda of Irwindale, in the third lane of the 
four-lane freeway, tried to avoid the car but then ran over its right front 
hood and dragged the passenger vehicle along as it swerved onto the south-bound 
side. 
</P>
<P>
 The tractor spilled about 20 gallons of its own diesel fuel onto the roadway, 
complicating efforts to clear the accident and move morning traffic along, 
Garrett said. All lanes were reopened at 11:43 a.m., he said. ABIGAIL GOLDMAN 
</P>
