<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXPERIMENTAL TWILIGHT RACING AT DEL MAR TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE DISTEL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While not quite following the lead of the Chicago Cubs out of the daylight and 
into the night, the Del Mar Thoroughbred Club will approach the edge of 
darkness today. 
</P>
<P>
 First post for an experimental twilight program, the track's first, will be 4 
p.m. The card will be shortened to eight races, the seventh being the featured 
Honey Fox Handicap, because of the flirtation with dusk.The last race is 
expected to be run at 7:25. 
</P>
<P>
 "If we're successful, I think we might be interested in a lighted program," 
said Dan Smith, Del Mar's director of marketing and media. "But I don't think 
we'd do it like Hollywood Park and go 7 to 11 (p.m.). I think we'd be more 
likely to start at 4 and not worry about running out of light with a nine-race 
program." 
</P>
<P>
 At present, Del Mar has no lights for racing. DAVE DISTEL 
</P>
</TEXT>
