<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE TIMES MUSIC INDEX: COMPANY TOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 STACKING UP SALES 
</P>
<P>
 Total album and single sales of CDs and cassettes for the week ended July 10, 
compared to week-ago and year-ago levels, in millions of units sold:  
</P>
<P>
 Latest week: Albums: 11.2 Singles: 2.0 
</P>
<P>
 Week-ago: Albums: 11.0 Singles: 2.0 
</P>
<P>
 Year-ago: Albums: 10.6 Singles: 2.7 Atop the Charts 
</P>
<P>
 Monthly record company market share as of July, based on units sold. This is 
an indicator of music company performance. Hits Magazine Tip of the Week 
</P>
<P>
 VH-1 is reporting a huge ratings increase for its "Stones TV" programming, for 
which the video channel preempted its regular 7 p.m-to-midnight schedule with 
Rolling Stones clips, interviews and reports from the band's "Voodoo Lounge" 
tour. "Stones TV" marks the first major programming move by the channel under 
new President John Sykes and Vice President Andy Schoun, who are attempting to 
remove VH-1 from the shadow of its more successful sister network, MTV. Among 
the channel's new goals is more active participation in the music industry. 
</P>
<P>
 Note: Hits magazine is a weekly music industry trade publication. 
