<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; EX-DISNEY FILM EXEC JOINS WARNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Warner Bros. named former Walt Disney Co. animation executive Jerry Davis as 
director of creative development for its feature animation department. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis was senior creative executive at Walt Disney Feature Animation, 
supervising such projects as the forthcoming "Toy Story."He previously was 
director of television for Landmark Entertainment Group. 
</P>
<P>
 * Carolyn Baker was named Warner Bros. Records vice president of A&R 
development for black music. 
</P>
<P>
 * Georgia O'Connor has been promoted to the new position of vice president of 
field marketing for Buena Vista Pictures Marketing. 
</P>
<P>
 * Michele DiLorenzo has been promoted to president of Viacom New Media in New 
York. 
</P>
<P>
 * Disney Publishing has announced the promotion of John Skipper to vice 
president. He will oversee all Disney U.S. magazine and book publishing 
operations. 
</P>
<P>
 * Alliance Communications named Michael Weisbarth executive vice president of 
television. 
</P>
<P>
 * Gordon Peil has been named senior vice president of affiliate relations for 
Westwood One Entertainment in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 * Universal Pictures' marketing and publicity divisions announced a number of 
promotions and hirings as part of an expansion program: 
</P>
<P>
 Dan Wolfe was promoted to vice president of creative advertising operations, 
and Pam Postrel and Mary Erickson were named directors of creative advertising. 
</P>
<P>
 Charlie Holland of Premiere magazine joins the studio as director of print 
advertising. Brenda Scarbrough was promoted to executive director of media. 
Cece Horwitch has left Miramax Films to become Universal's senior publicist. 
Elizabeth Gengl and Jeffrey Sakson have been promoted to publicity directors. 
</P>
<P>
 Elizabeth Brous has left Savoy Pictures to join Universal as a publicity 
director. Marilyn Moore was named director of field operations. John Polwrek 
was named vice president of national promotions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
