<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. BRIEFLY: FLUOR VICE CHAIRMAN KONTNY RESIGNS AFTER 29 YEARS AT THE 
ENGINEERING FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fluor Corp. said Thursday that its vice chairman, Vince Kontny, has decided to 
take early retirement after 29 years at the engineering giant. 
</P>
<P>
 Kontny, 57, said in a statement that he looking forward to spending more time 
with his family and on outside interests. 
</P>
<P>
 "I have mixed emotions leaving at this time, given the company's considerable 
success," Kontny said. Second-quarter net income for Fluor was $47.7 million, 
up 14% over the same period last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Fluor Chairman Les McCraw praised Kontny as having "made a significant 
contribution to the company, particularly with his participation in the 
creation of Fluor Daniel in 1986 and its growth since that time." 
</P>
</TEXT>
