<TEXT>
<P>
 Rockwell International Corp.: The company said that it, along with Hughes 
Aircraft Corp. and a Russian research and development institute, won a 
$4.7-million contract to help Russia modernize its air traffic management 
system by using satellites. 
</P>
<P>
 Seal Beach-based Rockwell and General Motors Corp.'s Hughes Aircraft unit will 
provide business training, technology and products for Russia to use in its air 
traffic management system. 
</P>
<P>
 The contract was awarded by the Defense Nuclear Agency under a U.S. Department 
of Defense program to assist selected Russian enterprises in converting their 
industrial capacity from building weapons to commercial enterprise. 
</P>
