<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pinnacle Micro Inc.: Shares of the Irvine maker of optical data-storage 
systems fell 17% Thursday after the company delayed reporting its 
second-quarter earnings.Pinnacle, which went public in June, 1993, did not 
release earnings when expected, but will release them by Aug. 15, said Scott 
Blum, the executive vice president. 
</P>
<P>
 He added that the company is considering changing next year the last day of 
its fiscal year to June 30 from Dec. 31. As a result, its auditor, Ernst & 
Young, is doing a more in-depth study of the company's 1994 performance to date 
than normal. The delay gave investors cause for concern, and the stock tumbled 
$2.75 in Nasdaq trading Thursday to close at $13 a share. 
</P>
