<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. NEWSMAKERS: CORAM HEALTHCARE NAMES PRESIDENT; 6 EXECUTIVES RESIGN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Patrick J. Fortune has been appointed president and chief operating officer 
of Coram Healthcare Corp. in Newport Beach, effective Aug. 15. He most recently 
served as corporate vice president of information management for Bristol-Meyers 
Squibb Co.Coram, which has announced plans to relocate its headquarters to 
Boulder, Colo., was formed as a result of the four-way merger last month of 
United T2 Medical, Curaflex Health Services, Medisys Inc. and HealthInfusion 
Inc. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition, the company said six executives have resigned. They are: Tom 
Haire, former chairman of T2 Medical; Tommy H. Carter, past president and chief 
operating officer of T2 Medical; Charles A. Laverty, Coram senior executive 
vice president and Curaflex's chairman, president and chief executive; Miles E. 
Gilman, Coram executive vice president and past chief executive of 
HealthInfusion; William J. Brummond, Coram vice president and former chief 
executive of Medisys, and W. Barry Tanner, past chief operating officer of 
HealthInfusion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
