<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: NATURE CALLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Want to get in tune with nature? Consider the Joseph Cornell Nature Awareness 
Family Workshop on Aug. 20, sponsored by the Laguna Art Museum. 
</P>
<P>
 Held in conjunction with the museum's current exhibit, "Fragile Ecologies," 
the 9 a.m. to noon workshop will begin with a morning hike through the Laguna 
Coast Wilderness Park. Cost is $15 a person and reservations are required. Call 
the museum's education department, (714) 494-8971. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Fragile Ecologies" exhibit focuses on ecological art and the 
interrelationships of earth, water and atmosphere. 
</P>
</TEXT>
